        <mxCell id="GG3aVVR33aSNDu_euWsj-54" parent="1" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Thermostat State Machine Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;The thermostat operates as a three‑state cyclic state machine consisting of &lt;strong style=&quot;&quot;&gt;OFF&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong style=&quot;&quot;&gt;HEAT&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong style=&quot;&quot;&gt;COOL&lt;/strong&gt;. Pressing the &lt;strong style=&quot;&quot;&gt;green button&lt;/strong&gt; advances the system to the next state in the sequence (OFF → HEAT → COOL → OFF). From any state, the &lt;strong style=&quot;&quot;&gt;red button&lt;/strong&gt; increases the setPoint and the &lt;strong style=&quot;&quot;&gt;blue button&lt;/strong&gt; decreases it, allowing the user to adjust the desired temperature at any time. In the &lt;strong style=&quot;&quot;&gt;HEAT&lt;/strong&gt; state, the thermostat compares the current temperature to the setPoint: if the temperature is below the setPoint, the red LED fades to indicate heating demand; otherwise, it remains solid. In the &lt;strong style=&quot;&quot;&gt;COOL&lt;/strong&gt; state, the blue LED fades when the temperature is above the setPoint and becomes solid once cooling is no longer required. In the &lt;strong style=&quot;&quot;&gt;OFF&lt;/strong&gt; state, all LEDs remain off and no heating or cooling behavior is active. This state machine ensures predictable, cyclic behavior and clear visual feedback through LED indicators.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="390" width="720" y="480" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
